        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Apparently pets that are charmed WITHOUT DC will be the same as regular summoned pets and will take zero exp if the player does damage to the mob.  Below is the question asked to Absor on the dev boards and the response to that question.</P><P>=========================================</P><P>Splendora-ROV wrote:<BR>Regarding pet changes, I notice you are differentiating between 'normal' pets and Dire Charm as far as the experience changes go. But what about 'normal' charm ? Will the regular pet rules apply in that case or will it be the same as Dire ?</P><P>---<BR>Actually, the differentiation is between Dire Charmed pets and all other pets.</P><P>Once something is charmed it is a pet.</P><P>So the regular rules will apply to charmed pets, with the exception of Dire Charmed pets, as noted above.</P><P>Alan<BR>---<BR>==========================================</P><P>Ozznusyen Zuulavv<BR>55th Defiler<BR>Brell Serilis</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
