        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, I like the changes a lot. </P><P>No matter what some of you think, balancing isn't just an issue for the level 60s in uberguilds. Admittedly, this isn't so much balancing as making life easier for everyone. The neutrality of pets (which I would point out is something we've been asking for) will help less-experienced guilds in pulling off raids in a happier way. How many times did you get pissed off when the raid leader wouldn't allow pets? Feared pets won't bring the whole zone on you anymore! There is very little chance of our pets breaking mez!</P><P>And just out of curiousity: for the ones who are complaining about Dire Charm, do you really have that many more AAP to get that what probably amounts to a 10% loss in efficiency is going to affect you terribly much? So maybe you'll end up spending a week or two extra to max out your AAP. Is it really so big a deal that you'd take this cause for celebration and turn it into a stone throwing contest instead?</P><P>Tenaiya Soulscorcher<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
